por.por_txt_cntn:
The overarching objective in this proposal is to relate regulation of the mechanosensitive Sost-Wnt/b-catenin pathway, specific to osteocyte-induced skeletal anabolism, and the relative tissue response to physical stimuli in the skeletons of species from three terrestrial vertebrate groups (reptiles, birds, mammals).





Objective #1: Characterize the tissue-level response of the tibiae in reptiles, birds, andmammals to similar applied functional strain levels.


Objective #2: Determine the contributions of mechanosensitive osteocytes and bone-forming osteoblasts to the tissue-level mechanobiological response of the tibia.


Objective #3: Characterize the osteocyte and osteoblast response to compressionloading in cortical bone organ cultures to establish the sensitivity of the osteocyte-osteoblast mechanism


